  "prompt": "How do I block/password protect content from my external hard disk from being copied or deleted?",
  "response": "Here are several methods to protect content on an external hard disk:\n\n1. File/Folder Level Protection:\n- Use Windows built-in encryption (BitLocker)\n- Use third-party encryption software like VeraCrypt\n- Set folder/file permissions\n- Use password-protected compressed archives\n\n2. Full Disk Encryption:\n- BitLocker (Windows)\n- FileVault (Mac)\n- VeraCrypt (Cross-platform)\n- Use disk encryption tools\n\n3. Software Solutions:\n- Create password-protected folders\n- Use file lock software like GiliSoft File Lock\n- Use disk protection software\n\n4. Hardware Solutions:\n- Use hardware-encrypted external drives\n- Get drives with built-in password protection\n- Use physical write-protection switches\n\n5. Access Control:\n- Set administrator passwords\n- Restrict user permissions\n- Use access control lists (ACLs)\n\n6. Advanced Options:\n- Use DRM software\n- Implement network-level access controls\n- Use secure cloud storage with permissions\n\nSpecific recommendations depend on:\n- Your operating system\n- Technical skill level\n- Specific protection needs\n- Budget\n\nWhich method sounds most suitable for your situation?",
